author: TrixieGoldenwing
text: I would have been roughly 36 weeks by now. Almost 1 month to welcoming my baby into this world. Each day that passes and gets closer and closer to when my due date would have been takes me deeper into this suffocating darkness. And now I have no comfort to help me through this.

author: TrixieGoldenwing
text: I am going to explode on or today my god.

author: TrixieGoldenwing
text: I had a charm reading done today by ginganinjatarot from TikTok. It was beautiful and she had such a warm and loving energy. Good things are to come and my fulfillment is coming. She was wonderful and informative. I highly recommend her for a reading https://t.co/SUjD5TV09C https://t.co/fZ4pG2d99E

author: TrixieGoldenwing
text: Laying on my couch, drinking wine, watching Disney and sobbing. I’m pathetic.

author: TrixieGoldenwing
text:
Today at work I encountered animals that I haven’t encountered up close before. While walking to my car a bald eagle landed 8 feet away from me. When I got back to work there was a pair of swans that flew over and landed in the lake. 

SPIRIT GUIDES WHAT DOES THIS MEAN?!?!?!?

author: TrixieGoldenwing
text:
I have been in survival mode since the end of February. I am so tired and I don’t know how to pull myself out of this. I’m masking again to the people around me. I am so close to giving up on everything. I can’t do this anymore . . . 

https://t.co/Yd9f7Fopex via @YouTube

author: TrixieGoldenwing
text:
I lost my chance to raise a beautiful child in a loving home. To have their father and me playing all of their games. Tucking them in, reading them stories, and teaching them the important life lessons. 
I would have given anything to bring my baby into this world.

author: TrixieGoldenwing
text:
I have absolutely been enjoying Bluey, but it also makes me so sad. The days I could have been watching this with the child I never got to hold. The toys and games I would have gifted. 

Seeing how Bandit and Chilli raise their children and play all of their games makes me sad.

author: TrixieGoldenwing
text: I started watching Bluey to try and make me feel even a little better, not make me sob harder . . . .

author: TrixieGoldenwing
